Package org.forgerock.openam.sm.datalayer.impl

Class SeriesTaskExecutorThread

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.forgerock.openam.sm.datalayer.impl.SeriesTaskExecutorThread
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable
    public class SeriesTaskExecutorThread
extends Object
implements Runnable
    Responsible for processing CTS Tasks asynchronously. This implementation will draw a task from an allocated BlockingQueue and makes no assumptions about the nature of the task, or the queue from which it is drawing tasks. This decoupled design is intended to ensure that each TaskProcessor can be run as part of a thread pool, and process tasks in a continuous fashion. Thread Policy: This runnable will respond to Thread interrupts and will exit cleanly in the event of an interrupt.
    See Also:
    Task, TaskFactory
